 Police in Despatch on Friday opened an inquest docket after fire fighters found the body of a man in the debris of a burnt-out shack in the town. “At around 04:30am, police were summoned to a scene of shack that was engulfed in flames in Nkosini Street, Despatch,” described police spokesperson, Sergeant Majola Nkohli. “Fire fighters recovered the burnt-out body of Thembani Maqebuka (27). “Police opened an inquest docket for investigation.” Sergeant Nkohli said that at  this stage, the cause of the fire is unknown. 